channel.title: Help i got always error
channel.description:
why the hell i got always this:
Failed when compiling Line 50: [Error] (53:10): Duplicate identifier 'UpChars' in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 3.05\includes\ssi2.txt
ALWAYS !
and i got always this:
Line 148: [Error] (156:4): Unknown identifier 'IsTextAt2' in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 3.05\includes\boxbreaker2.txt
why? please help me.. this is first time when i use scar/script

item.title: Help i got always error
item.dc:creator: @AGENT_83 AGENT 83
item.description:
@AGENT_83 wrote:

I’m going to say that its an include-SRL conflict and they both use the same vars. If you’re using scripts with SSI2, you should really focus more on getting SRL then getting rid of duplicate identifiers. Most scripts that use that are outdated anyway.
